name: ACID FAST "Rabid Moon" vinyl LP
description:
Note: This is a pre-order. Shipping begins January 7th. 

Following their debut "Weird Date" 7"EP and a couple of successful tours, the band presents their anxiously awaited full-length. Acid Fast play scraggly and jangly, melodic and energetic, fuzzy and catchy Bay Area punk that nods to the past, and embraces its future. Competing and complimentary Male/Female vocals add just the right finishing touch to the riffs, so what you have is an album that totally sticks to your ribs! For fans of: Jawbreaker, Superchunk, Swearin, Big Kids.

Europeans may also order from Adagio830.

name: DECEMBER $1.50 Add-On Sale!!
description:
Purchase $10.00 worth of ANY items in our webstore and you can add any of these releases for only $1.50 each, plus only $1.00 postage added in the USA!! (And only a couple bucks more for international!!)  So add as many as you want, it's a great deal. But you MUST spend at least $10.00 on other items!

Choose from any of the following 12 releases:

options.name: 4-WAY SPLIT cassette (w/Echo Hey Hello, Groundcover and more)
Teenage Cool Kids/Daniel Striped Tiger split 7"

name: CARRIE FUCILE "Subtext" cassette
description:
Essentially this is one of the most interesting "noise" recordings we've heard in a long time. It's haunting, erotic, mesmerizing, and completely unique. A limited edition of only 80 copies. Pro-duplicated cassettes, Pro-printed full-color covers.

From Carrie's blog: "I recorded several individuals singing a popular song of their choice. I then edited the files to my liking. The edited files only use portions of the recordings where words were not articulated. These leftover sounds consists of various
inhalations and utterances. My interest lies in exploring what the hidden sounds of a vocal recording can possibly tell us about unexpressed desires that constitute part of our attraction to popular music."

name: SED NON SATIATA "Mappo" gatefold vinyl LP
description:
The third full-length from France's amazing SED NON SATIATA is finally here! Recorded at Electrical Audio (Albini's studio) and mastered by Alan Douches at West West Side, not to mention  representing the first recording with their new 5-piece line-up, this experience is nothing short of overwhelming. SNS have achieved a huge sound here, full of emotional and sonic subtleties and bludgeoning post-hardcore rock alike. Housed in a beautiful gatefold cover, pressed on lovely red+clear smoke mixed color vinyl. Comes with a digital download card. 

Europeans, please order from Echo Canyon or Adagio830

name: NAH "Otheration" full-length cassette
description:
Beats. Soundscapes. Noise. Rhymes. Drums. Samples. This collection of music from NAH (aka Mike from 1994!) is challenging and inventive. It's hypnotic and catchy. For fans of industrial and electronic music, hip-hop, and hardcore alike.

A limited run of Pro-duplicated, Pro-printed cassettes w/full-color covers.

name: ABJECT OBJECT "Romance" vinyl LP
description:
French punk played with melody, aggression, hooks, and energy.  Hard to sit still while listening to this one!  Featuring members of Sed Non Satiata.  Awesome cover art with a black inner-sleeve, and inside cover printing (see pics!), finish out what is sure to be one of the most diverse records we've done on the label. Mastered by Carl Saff.

A limited number of copies available here in the USA. 
Co-release with Echo Canyon and Flower of Carnage.

name: AMBER "Lovesaken" vinyl LP
description:
LOVESAKEN, which is the first full-length from AMBER, is an epic, riff-soaked record of five songs stretched perfectly over 35 minutes. At times uplifting and yet with a somber tone, almost bittersweet, this is a record to drown in..like tears...like rain.  AMBER hail from Marburg, Germany, and play post-hardcore, post-rock, with heavy sludge parts and deep atmospheric melodies. The vocals are anguished and apocalyptic.  Rock this shit if you like FALL OF EFRAFA, CULT OF LUNA, ENVY or ISIS. 

BE SURE TO CHOOSE YOUR VINYL COLOR.

name: SECRET SMOKER "Terminal Architecture" vinyl LP
description:
Baton Rouge, LA, has produced a trio of musicians that seem to have come to the 2010's via the 1990's, and they call themselves Secret Smoker.  This debut LP has the sonic, political, and emotional hallmarks of bands like Hoover, 400 Years, Amber Inn, Wolves, and Sleepytime Trio, while maintaining a discernible identity of its own.  Featuring former members of We Are The Living, and active participants of the Hungry Ghost Collective, these guys are intent upon driving home passionate "emo" the way you knew it before the shopping malls got a hold of it.  If you like your music with movement and meaning, dig in!  

Each record comes with a digital download card, and is available on either Clear or limited White vinyl.  First 50 pre-orders get a poster and sticker! (from Protagonist only)

This is a split-label effort with Adagio830 in Germany, so European folks can order from them.

name: CARRION SPRING "Indiscretions Vol. 1" full-length cassette
description:
Screamo is a nasty word in this camp, and "emo" has lost its meaning entirely...so just what is Carrion Spring? An emotionally chaotic, intricate, melodic, pummeling, hardcore punk band. Maybe. But who cares...after hearing this cassette, you'll wonder how you missed out on this band in the first place.  This is 7 songs for fans of: Saetia, Portraits of Past, Capacities, Beau Navire. Mastered by Will Killingsworth (Ampere, Vaccine, etc) at Dead Air Studios. 

Pro-duplicated, Pro-printed cassettes, with full-color covers.

name: WITS END / TREMBLING HANDS split 7" vinyl
description: Hailing from Norway, Wits End shows an emotional side with two tracks reflecting the  seasons. The opener ‘summer’ is Wits End channeling Christie Front Drive... Mellow guitars, dual vocals and the mid 90s all over again. Then ‘winter’, albeit a slow song, brings back the heavier lyrical topics and more driving sound. Sweden's favorites, Trembling Hands (mem of Suis La Lune), deliver one song from the same recording session as the self titled 7″ last year. Heavy emotional stuff like Majority Rule or Malady. Stateside copies come in a very nice screen-printed cover.

name: SED NON SATIATA - s/t vinyl LP
description:
This (probably) the final recorded output from these incredible French musicians.  There are 8 songs totaling over 30 minutes of emotionally gut-wrenching post hardcore here...a final statement that will leave you wishing for more.  This monumental recording will take you on a journey: from instrumental passages that lull you into calm reflection, up through furious swells of passionate hardcore pounding away at your speakers.

Another limited imported pressing, this run of the record is available on deep-sea blue colored vinyl, with beautifully printed fold-over covers and slightly new black/white artwork.

name: CAPACITIES "The Unexamined Life" vinyl 12"
description:
*This is a pre-order for the repress. Covers will arrive in about 10 days and shipments will begin shortly thereafter!*

One-sided 12" of unapologetic hardcore from members of Black Kites, The Saddest Landscape, Less Life, and more.  Heavy, fast, and pissed at the world.  Twelve songs that pull no punches. The B-side is screened with glow in the dark ink! Second pressing is limited to only 300 copies.  

Split release with How Soon Is Now Records.

name: FLASHLIGHTS "I'm Not Alone" vinyl LP
description:
So what do you get when a bunch of young folks start playing catchy songs that seem to mix the quirkiness of Superchunk with the best parts of your favorite pop-punk bands?  Flashlights.  This Florida foursome's debut LP is your new favorite thing, and you'll dance and sing along in your living room while listening - we promise!!          

MIXED-COLOR vinyl limited to around 100 copies, exclusive to the label, for mail-order only.  YELLOW-ISH colored vinyl everywhere else.   Digital download included.

T-shirts available too!

name: SECRET SMOKER "Prizm" T-shirt
description:
Printed by the band on Hanes Nano brand shirts, these are super soft.  American Apparel style feel and sizing. 

Light blue ink on dark blue shirt.  Center front print, with small Protagonist logo on upper back.  Available in sizes Adult Small, Adult Medium, and Adult Large.

name: SED NON SATIATA "Tour" T-shirt
description:
Sed Non Satiata "USA Tour 2012" shirt, front print. 
Printed on Gildan Heavy Cotton Preshrunk 100% cotton shirts. 

Bright green or light blue shirt with black ink.

name: FLASHLIGHTS "Raccoon" T-shirt
description:
Light blue shirt with navy blue print....
...or...
Yellow shirt with dark blue print

Fruit of the Loom 50/50.  

Available in sizes:
Youth-Large, Adult Small, Adult Medium, Adult Large.

name: WET NURSE "Daily Whatever" full-length cassette
description:
A Florida trio that take punk and melody to an exciting place, the girls in WET NURSE have really hit that spot with their debut full-length.  Whether it's sneering garage-punk or sweet vocal harmonies, these 11 songs are infectious all the way through.  Fans of the Donnas, Bangs, the GoGo's, the Ramones, and Go Sailor should take note.  

Pro-duplicated, Pro-printed cassettes, with full-color covers.

name: "4-Way Split" full-length cassette (Featuring: Tacobonds, Echo Hey Hello, etc)
description:
8 songs total: 2 songs each by 2 bands from Tokyo, Japan (Tacobonds & Groundcover) and 2 bands from Baltimore, MD (Weekends & Echo Hey Hello). Tacobonds is a trio that plays dance punk, & Groundcover sounds like a mixture of Tortoise and the Boredoms. Weekends is a guitar/drums duo playing dirty garage/art rock, and Echo Hey Hello play instrumental post-rock. Pro-style cassettes. Full-color covers.  

Links:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KflT2ugLWjQ
http://vimeo.com/30580083
http://weekendsbaltimore.bandcamp.com
http://echoheyhello.bandcamp.com

name: ACID FAST "Weird Date" vinyl 7"
description:
Four songs of lo-fi, melodic, Bay-Area punk, with complimenting male/female vocals.  Four super catchy songs that will have you humming them long after the record stops.  

Members of BIG KIDS.  

Hand-screened covers.  Clear vinyl limited to 300 copies!

name: COPING "Nope" lmtd edition test-press LP
description:
A limited edition test-press version of the "Nope" LP only available from the band at their last show on Dec 22nd, 2012...or by direct mail-order from us here at the label.

Each record comes in a "recycled" and individually painted, stamped, and numbered chipboard cover.  Each one is unique.  There will only be about 105 of these in existence...so act fast!

name: CHILD MEADOW "Crispy BBQ Tofu Burger" vinyl LP
description:
Featuring members of Bokanovsky, this French band delivers emotional hardcore the way we've come to love from Europe.  The music travels peaks and valleys throughout, with passion and energy. Hand-screened covers and inserts, black vinyl, and uniquely-styled artwork make this a beautiful record on every level.  

Limited import manufactured in France, so get it while you can!

name: BLACK KITES "Animal Liberation" T-shirt
description:
White print on front of black shirt.
Fruit Of The Loom Heavy Cotton.
Available in sizes: 
Adult Small, Adult Medium, Adult Large, Adult X-Large

name: BIG KIDS "Phone Home" vinyl LP
description: The sophomore LP from BIG KIDS is exactly what you need...urgent and passionate music with more than enough melody to keep you singing along, and just enough jagged edges to remind you it's real. Recorded in a flurry of stress and creative energy, the songs here are a step forward for the band and the listener, but hardly a departure from what connected so many people to their first record. Listen to this loud, and with friends. European folks: this is a split-label release with ADAGIO830 from Germany, so if you don't see your country listed in our shipping options, please try ordering from them. Each copy comes with a digital download card.

name: ZANN "X" vinyl 7" w/bonus full-length CD
description:
Hailing from Germany, Zann have been creating passionate and punishing sXe hardcore for 10 years now...and this record is a testament to their energy.  With a little nod to 90's bands like Unbroken, Acme, Rorschach and Chokehold, they have forged a sound of their own and an international reputation for no-nonsense hardcore with brains and brawn.  

Packaged in a beautifully printed and letter-pressed cover, along with a full-length CD containing 15 additional songs.  Thick black vinyl completes the assembly, and early orders receive a sticker too!

name: BLACK KITES "Songs Written While Things Were Changing" LP
description:
This intense New Jersey trio return with their 2nd full-length LP, and it is nothing short of a hardcore masterpiece.  An emotionally devastating assault both lyrically and aurally, you'll need several listens just to take it all in!  

Copies come on multi-colored vinyl or traditional black, and all come with a digital download card too!

name: BIG KIDS "Hoop Dreams" vinyl LP
description:
Third pressing available now!

We are very happy to announce the debut LP from Oakland's BIG KIDS.  This record is 9 tracks that capture the bliss of playing music with your good friends, touring in a shitty van, playing killer house shows, and seeing life through the prism of punk rock.  Melodies and dirt, sing-alongs and feedback, relationships and ideas...all are represented here.  If you dig Small Brown Bike, Bear Vs. Shark, or New Bruises, this band is going to be your next fave.   Comes with a digital download too!

The project is a split-label effort between Protagonist and the fine people at TopShelf Records.

name: TEENAGE COOL KIDS/DANIEL STRIPED TIGER split 7" vinyl
description:
An odd couple in some ways, and perfect mate in others, TCK and DST have been talking about this record forever.  And here it is: two new songs from each band!  The record is "party" themed and comes on colored vinyl with great full-color packaging and a digital download.  Super limited to only 440 copies available form the labels...so act fast...if this record is re-pressed it will not be done in the same way at all.

Limited red vinyl available from us.  Blue available from Clean Plate Records (or from us in a limited quantity!)

BE SURE TO CHOOSE YOUR VINYL COLOR!

name: ALGERNON CADWALLADER "Fun" 7" vinyl w/bonus CDep
description:
The long-awaited 3rd pressing is here!

The Philly dudes are back, and now you can get their most recent offering of melodic, quirky pop goodness on lovely 7" vinyl.  This project contains 3 new songs on the record itself, plus a BONUS additional CDep with 3 more unreleased songs!  That's right, a total of 6 new songs that will please the pants right off you if you're into Cap'n Jazz, house-parties, Braid, sing-alongs, and FUN.  


NOW AVAILABLE ON A (very) LIMITED RUN OF LIME FOAM COLORED  VINYL!  As well as black, available from the band or from us.

name: TEENAGE COOL KIDS "Queer Salutations" Vinyl LP
description:
This is it, finally!  A vinyl version of the first CD that made you fall in love with a group of four goofy punks from Denton, Texas.  All the songs you sing along to already are here, remastered specially for vinyl by Josh Bonati.  Packaged with full color covers and inserts, and colored vinyl too.  A limited amount of orange vinyl (only about 200 copies) will be available to the first people who pre-order, and the rest of this small pressing is on ice blue vinyl.  A bunch of the first orders will also get a free poster and button.  Act fast, these will sell like hot cakes for sure!

BE SURE TO CHOOSE YOUR VINYL COLOR.

name: SUIS LA LUNE / OSCEOLA vinyl split 7"
description: 2 new raging songs from Osceola and 1 new epic event from Suis La Lune here on the split 7inch.  The idea for the record came about when the bands toured together and now it has finally become a reality... And if you saw either of these bands on that tour, you know you need this record!!  50 copies of limited clear vinyl, the rest are on black.  A split label release with our friends at Escucha and Fasaden.

name: TEENAGE COOL KIDS "Foreign Lands" 180gm LP
description:
Picking up where their debut CD left off, and maturing quite a bit in the process, Teenage COOL KIDS have produced something amazing here:  12 new songs that will be stuck in your head from the first moment you hear them!  

This new album has nods toward an early Built To Spill sound, but the band has really grown into their own melodic take on indie-pop-punk-rock.  Packaged beautifully and pressed on thick 180gram audiophile quality vinyl, you don't wanna miss out on the first pressing here.  Each record also comes with a free digital download!!

**DON'T FORGET TO CHOOSE THE COLOR YOU WANT**

name: ADORNO "Year One" Limited Edition CD
description: Hailing from Portugal, the guys in ADORNO play passionate hardcore with a melodic edge.  This release compiles all of their vinyl output from 2007-08 and id their first stateside offering.  The 9 songs here will rock for fans of Amanda Woodward, End Of A Year, At The Drive In, Daitro and Husker Du.  Packaging is hand-screened and hand-numbered in a limited edition of 300, so act now!

name: ...WHO CALLS SO LOUD s/t vinyl 12" EP
description: This Bay Area band is exploring new territory on this release.  Soundscape experimentation coupled with their pounding, pleading emotional hardcore make up this new EP, and it's sure to please fans of their recent 2x10" from earlier this year.  Featuring ex-members of Funeral Diner and Portraits of Past, you can get an idea of the passionate direction contained herein.  Available on Green or Black/Green half and half colored vinyl.

name: TEENAGE COOL KIDS "Queer Salutations" CD
description: These young guys from Denton, Texas are making music fun again! On their debut full-length they come forward to give you 11 songs with a tremendous amount of wit, pop sensibility, and ass-shakin’ goodness. Welcome to the soundtrack of the best house-party show you’ve been to this year! A must for fans of MENEGUAR, DINOSAUR JR, early BUILT TO SPILL, and JAWBREAKER.

name: TOWERS - self titled full length cassette
description: This is the cassette version of TOWERS full length vinyl release from late 2007 (on Electric Human Project). This Philadelphia band has been touring like crazy over the last few years, and has opened peoples eyes to some seriously outrageous tunes. Get this if you’re into a psychedelic and crushingly heavy hardcore experience…

name: PYRAMIDS "Through the Hourglass" CD
description: A second full-length release fron this trio, and the journey continues… Stories of time travel and personal discovery are woven through intricate and melodic, yet crushing hardcore. Beautiful packaging with a die-cut cover, limited to 500 copies. Fans of CITY OF CATEPILLAR, HOOVER,YAPHETT KOTTO and A PETAL FALLEN take note!

name: IN FIRST PERSON / STORM The BASTILLE split LP
description: This is what hardcore should be all about: passion, movement, energy, and heavy freakin’ riffs!! These two bands are going have you moshing in your living room and tearing down “the state” while you spin this new record….Limited pink/white vinyl available only from the band or label directly – so don’t hesitate. For fans of: CONVERGE, 108, HIS HERO IS GONE, DISEMBODIED.

name: SOUVENIR'S YOUNG AMERICA "September Songs" 12"
description: Epic soundscapes, pounding rythms, and haunting melodies…the soundtrack to being lost in the desert on a quest for personal salvation. This is post-hardcore rock at it’s finest, with inventive instrumentation and delicately crafted power. Pressed on thick, high quality vinyl, this 12” comes in a beautifully silk-screened 3 color cover and is limited to 500 copies! If you like ISIS, RED SPARROWES, JESU, CULT OF LUNA, or MONO, this is your new favorite record.

name: CARRION SPRING "A Short History of Decay" vinyl LP
description:
This is the debut LP from Portland, Oregon's own Carrion Spring. An emotional hardcore feast for fans of You and I, Beau Navire, Saetia, Coma Regalia. Members of Kidcrash and Logs. On orange vinyl.

Released by BEAR Records.

name: CARA NEIR "Portals to a Better.." vinyl LP
description:
Texas blackened hardcore duo Cara Neir return with “Portals to a Better, Dead World”, their first full length to appear on vinyl. Fans of the band won’t be disappointed as its Cara Neir at their best. “Portals…” is full of instantly catchy songs and ferocious riffs. Hand-numbered covers.

Released via Halo Of Flies.

name: THROWERS "Prosaic Materialists..." vinyl 10"
description:
"There must be something in the air or in the water in Leipzig...maybe it's the Eastern German history, the lack of perspectives or the hopelessness in those eastern wastelands... after bands such as Zann, Perth Express, Black Freighter, and more ... all came from that city.  Here's the next killer band: THROWERS"

Released by Vendetta Records

name: SED NON SATIATA "Mappo" cassette
description: Same as the gatefold LP, but in cassette form. Cool fold-out packaging!

name: CELLOS "Bomb Shelter" vinyl LP
description: Every once in a while  band will come out of nowhere and just flat out knocks you on your ass.  CELLOS are definitely one of those bands. Stewing in the same sludgey, riff infected cesspool as mid to late 90's heavy hitters like Karp, Unwound, Godheadsilo and Unsane; this Windsor, Ontario three-piece write some of the most punishingly awesome tunes you'll ever hear.  This is harsh, destructive music where warm, fuzzy riffs are king and loud, noisy feedback is lauded as they melt, slice, and demolish each song into acute ear fucking precision.  Nods to the Melvins and Black Sabbath are pretty much essential as foundational purveyors in the genre.  And CELLOS fit right in with the above mentioned artists as a band that's pushing the boundaries of extremely heavy music, one crudely bashed low-end hit at a time.  Really can't recommend this one enough.

name: COMA REGALIA "En Sperata" vinyl LP
description:
Coma Regalia's debut full-length contains 10 amazing tracks of post-hardcore/ screamo/ emo/ whatever-you-wanna-call-it that are just amazing! Some might call it a concept album, but all in all, it's an experience. Awesome colored vinyl with a screen-printed b-side and hand-screened cover. 

Released by Middle-Man Records and How Soon Is Now.

name: BURNING BRIGHT "Domesday" vinyl LP
description: Fuck yeah! Members of Aussitot Mort bring you dark, melodic, and intricate hardcore. For fans of metal, crust, and heavy hardcore alike. The damn Europeans just seem to do it right!

name: ESTATES "Gleam" vinyl LP
description:
Amazing debut LP from this Milwaukee band. 
For fans of Hum, Nirvana, and Mineral. 
Recommended.

name: WAR EMBLEM "Demo" Cassette
description: Killer hardcore from Philly.  5 songs of angst and energy. For fans of Born Against, Citizens Arrest, Rorschach, and crucial political hardcore.

name: ENEWETAK "Easy Rider Sessions, Vol 3" vinyl 7"
description: Recorded back on October 31, 2003 and originally slated for release on Crawlspace Records, this three song single finally sees the light of day. Features hand-stamped inner paper sleeve.

name: TERROR BIRD "Secret Rituals" vinyl LP
description:
"A new Terror Bird LP is something to savour, and 'Secret Rituals' scans and sounds like a greatest hits set. terror bird are a canadian group based on some fascinating contradictions and revolving around the powerful, affecting voice of nikki never. emerging with bedroom-forged cassettes on night people records, never added synth players and drummers as she went on, via releases on la station radar and night school, finally arriving at this point - a harder-hitting synth-goth masterpiece in 'secret rituals.' gone are the reservations and shyness of the straight-to-4 track songs of old and in their place is a forceful, immediate collection of songs that showcase her precise and emotive voice. tracks like 'thrill killer' are 80s goth pop songs re-imagined for the 21st century underground, insistent and propulsive, 'secret rituals' is a lush, dark gem and tracks like 'if we escape' are heroic, doomed-youth anthems for souls running from an impending doom, overfull but still pumping. the production is clearer than before, the passion intensified."

Released by ADAGIO830 Records

name: ROCKET REDUCRERS "s/t" vinyl LP
description: Garage rock.

name: TORTURE LOVE - Demo cassette
description:
Lo-fi, fuzzed out, electronic-infused darkwave that will appeal to fans of Bahaus, Joy Division, Teledrome, etc.  Comes in a handmade package.  Less than 100 made. 

One of our favorite releases of 2012.

name: CAFFEINE PATCH "demo" cassette
description:
From the basements of Allston, MA, straight to your brain. Loud, fast, meaningful hardcore.  Mosh in your living room.  For fans of Drop Dead, Natural Law, Capacities. Goes best with coffee.

Released by BEAR Records.

name: CAINO "Exegesis" vinyl LP
description: CAINO is a melodic crust trio from Palermo, Italy. Formerly members of Values Intact, L.E.A.R.N. and Cadaver Mutilator, they started painstaking research into religion and music that led them to a dark, melodic core into the powerful crust music rhythms and sludge thickness. CAINO’s “Exegesis” speaks both about the lies that religion took over mankind in history, and the daily lobotomy that people’s ignorance still suffers. “Exegesis” is limited to 300 copies.  Comes with printed inner sleeve.

name: BIRTH "s/t" vinyl LP
description: Devastatingly punishing debut here from Chicago dirtbags BIRTH!  Bathed in the same filth as Brainbombs, Drunks With Guns, Flipper and Big Black; BIRTH take cro-magnon riffs and shred 'em to bits as the sky collapses around 'em and they're buried in a pile of smoldering barbed wire. Think heavy, sludgey as fuck, proto punk that sounds like the Electric Eeels covering the Stooges using Sabbath's gear if it were stolen from a scrap yard and made out of knives. Brutally harsh landscapes where beating the shit out of your instruments is therapy and masochism is fun.  Ex members of Brain Handle.  Artwork by Ilth (Daily Void, Functional Blackouts).

name: PROTESTANT "Reclamation" vinyl LP
description:
5 songs in about 20 minutes of dark fucking hardcore punk.
Recorded at Howl Street Recordings and mastered by Carl Saff. 

Released by Halo Of Flies.

name: ADORNO "Year Two" vinyl LP
description:
“Hailing from Portugal, Adorno play passionate hardcore with a melodic edge. The band started as a group of 4 friends who create powerful, energetic melodic post hardcore with a message and lots of heart.  Noisy, distorted, melodic, beautiful, emotive, and sad sounding music. At times, it’s really hard to categorize the band’s sound. The songs are genuine and honest and it’s rare when a band like this comes along and sticks so close to how this style should sound, but Adorno has accomplished this sound to perfection. Fans of 1000 Travels Of Jawarhalal, Hot Cross, and Comadre take note!!! The songs on this LP are the songs from the band’s split 7″ with Black Heart Rebellion, their split 7″ with Eric Ayotte, the split 12″ with Sugartown Cabaret, their track from the Connections compilation, and one unreleased song.” – elementary revolt 

11 songs. Comes with: Hand-screened poly bag and CD of the songs too!  Released on SHOVE Records from Italy.

name: "A Summer Tour With" book (Algernon Cadwallader, Snowing, 1994!)
description:
"asummertourwith..." is a collection of photographs taken while ALGERNON CADWALLADER, SNOWING, and 1994!, traversed the USA over a 6 week period. Most of them were taken by the drummer of Snowing, Brian "Bean" Baksa. Some were added by Ross "Baby Britches" Brazuk.

80 pages
8.5"x8.5
Foil stamped cover.
Letterpressed book mark.

Limited to 200 copies.

name: ITTO self titled 10" vinyl
description:
Chicago's own ITTO rises from the ashes of Suffix. They dabble in the same sonic territory as Suffix with a heavy math rock, and screamo hardcore influence. For fans of Suffix, Beau Navire and Suis La Lune. 

On ADAGIO830 and Forever Escaping Boredom Records.

name: ALASKAN "The Weak & The Wounded" vinyl LP
description:
For the first time ever, Alaskan’s, “The Weak And The Wounded” is available on vinyl. Originally reserved for digital and tape release only, this EP was one of the main reasons The Treaty Oak Collective, as a label, came about.

4 tracks of ceaseless, pummeling sludge/post-metal. You’ll break the dial off of your preamp trying to turn this up louder and louder. Interspersed with samples from Session 9, this album is chilling to say the least. 

Released on Shove Records from Italy, and more.

name: LITTLE GOLD "On The Knife" vinyl LP
description:
"Christian DeRoeck spent most of the past decade in the band Meneguar. In late 2006, He and bandmate Jeremy Earl decided to combine their bedroom recordings and release them together, as Woods. They recorded two albums together and toured the US and Europe. In early 2008, for several reasons, Christian left both bands.

He spent the summer of 2008 working as a carpenter in eastern Long Island. Inhabiting a tiny basement room, he began working on the songs that shape On The Knife. In the fall he moved back to Brooklyn and teamed up with his old friend, multi-instrumentalist Dylan Edrich (Chain and the Gang), and Little Gold was born.

Recorded to tape at Emandee Studio in Brooklyn, On the Knife is a deeply personal take on love and loss, and was very much shaped by Christian’s departure from his previous bands. Like his earlier work with Woods, the songwriting is earnest, and of course there are a few indulgent headphone tracks as well.

Now joined by stand-up drummer Patty Conway, Little Gold has begun to incorporate more improvisational and psychedelic sounds into their mellow, country-rock oeuvre, and in the process are becoming a notable live act around NYC."

Released by ADAGIO830

name: AMBER "Demo" Cassette
description:
Epic, heavy, and melodic postmetal/post hardcore from Germany.
This is a repress of the self released Cdr from 2012.
A must for fans of Aussitot Mort, Fall of Efrafra, Cult of Luna. 
5 songs. 35min on pro-duplicated tapes. 4 panel jcard. 

Released by Halo Of Flies.

name: BRAIN TUMORS "s/t" vinyl LP
description: Minneapolis degenerates BRAIN TUMORS spit back with another angry ripper.  Pure menacing HC barked over punishing barbaric thrash.   Rippin' guitar work all over this fucker hammering out some of the most raw and uncompromising music you'll ever hear.  Mean music that's meant to hurt.  And it does.  If you dig shit like NEGATIVE APPROACH, GAUZE, LIP CREAM, or Clevo scums like, 9 Shocks Terror and The Inmates, this ones pretty much essential.  Total face ripper all the way.

name: ELDERS "Blind Rage" vinyl LP
description:
"Twelve tracks of violence disguised as music from the wild west."
King of the Monsters Records

Black vinyl.

name: CRYBABY "Coming Undone" vinyl 7"
description:
THEE legendary Ed Mcnulty of Nona returns to vinyl at last!
West Chester's newest sons give you 4 moody melodic pop songs on this debut 7". They sound like a less emo Snowing and a less poppy Spraynard, but I think the fans of both bands would really like this one. 

Released by Square of Opposition Records

name: JUNGBLUTH "Part Ache" vinyl LP
description:
Dark, pummeling, political hardcore from Germany. Ex-members of Alpinist. Lyric inserts are a bunch of individual postcards, and the covers are reverse-board printed. Fucking great all around!

Released on Halo of Flies Records and Vendetta.

name: COME ON DIE YOUNG s/t vinyl 7"
description:
COME ON DIE YOUNG delivers a high-spirited pummeling of melodic guitars, pulsing beat and charged scream. Garnering comparisons to bands like HOT WATER MUSIC, STRIKE ANYWHERE, GLASS & ASHES, LIFETIME and LEATHERFACE. This record comes with a digital download and is limited to 250 copies. 100 on red. 

MAN IN DECLINE RECORDS.

Red vinyl.

name: HORDES "Abarognosis" vinyl 7"
description:
Ten track vinyl debut from California's HORDES. Bludgeoning and merciless hardcore. The new breed of power violence is upon us. For fans of Infest, Man Is The Bastard, Lack of Interest, etc. On orange vinyl. 

Released by King Of The Monsters.

name: GEHENNA "Upon The Grave Hill" vinyl LP
description:
One of hardcore's most notorious and vicious bands. After releasing records on A389, CrimethInc, Crawlspace and Area 51, GEHENNA return with another devastating blast of uncompromising, metallic hardcore that is as ugly as it is sincere. No punches pulled music that is a sonic bombardment that will appeal to fans of Unruh, Catharsis, and Enewetak. Comes with poster insert.

KING OF THE MONSTERS RECORDS.

Blue vinyl, limited to 550

name: ROYAL MONSTERS "Blackwater" vinyl 7"
description:
Follow up to their single on New Age Records. Featuring ex-members of Where Eagles Dare, Landmine Marathon, George Moshington and Get Destroyed, Royal Monsters deliver four tracks that infuse punk with hardcore, metal and thrash, creating a desperate, dark and furious sound.  *Features guest vocals by Sean Bonnette from Andrew Jackson Jihad.


KING OF THE MONSTERS REOCRDS

Black vinyl, Limited to 330 copies.

name: OSS "demo" vinyl 7"
description:
Featuring vocals by Frank Hanney of MK-Ultra and Fourteen Or Fight, this short lived AZ bands demo was limited to 100 copies and disappeared almost as fast as they did. This seven inch collects all three songs from the demo, housed in an awesome custom die-cut sleeve.

Standard version comes on black vinyl and is limited to 500 copies.
On King Of The Monsters Records.

name: CHILD MEADOW "Rad" vinyl 7"
description:
First US release for this French emotional hardcore band.
Awesome hand-screened covers on chipboard.
Limited to only 300 copies.  Black vinyl.

Released on Affinity Index Records.

name: AMANDA WOODWARD "La Decadence de la Decadence" LP/CD
description:
We unearthed just a few copies of the long OOP record by French "emo" stalwarts, Amanda Woodward.  Also some copies on CD.

Green Vinyl, or Compact Disc.  On Code Of Ethics Records.
